   170	  ci-wait:
   171	    description: Wait for the remote CI run to finish.
   172	    program: ".rhei/check-ci.sh"
   173	    poll:
   174	      interval: 5m
   175	      max_attempts: 12
   176	```
   177	
   178	| Field | Type | Required | Description |
   179	|-------|------|----------|-------------|
   180	| `interval` | duration string | Yes | Minimum wall-clock wait between attempts (e.g., `30s`, `5m`, `1h`). The `--parallel` slot is released during the wait. |
   181	| `max_attempts` | integer | Yes | Upper bound on total attempts for this state within one task lifetime. Must be ≥ `1`. |
   182	
   183	### Semantics
   184	
   185	- **Attempt counter.** `poll.max_attempts` replaces the `visits` cap for the state. The same `metadata.tasks.<id>.stateVisits.<state-name>` counter records attempts; the counter starts at `1` on first entry and increments on every self-loop re-entry, identical to the `visits` accounting in [Transitions Specification — Counted Loops](rhei-transitions.spec.md#counted-loops).
   186	- **Retry signal.** Any self-loop transition (`from: X, to: X`) selected by the normal transition-matching rules is interpreted as "not done yet." The engine persists `metadata.tasks.<id>.pollNextAttemptAt.<state-name> = now() + interval`, releases the slot, and stops working this task for this pass. On later passes the task is excluded from the ready set until `pollNextAttemptAt` has elapsed.
   187	- **Exit.** Any non-self-loop transition exits the state normally and clears both `pollNextAttemptAt.<state-name>` and `stateVisits.<state-name>` for that state.
   188	- **Exhaustion.** When `stateVisits.<state-name> >= poll.max_attempts`, the engine will *not* execute a self-loop transition even if one matches. Instead it re-evaluates transitions and picks the first matching non-self-loop. The recommended pattern is an explicit exhaustion transition:
   189	  ```yaml
   190	  - from: ci-wait
   191	    to: ci-gave-up
   192	    condition: pollAttempts >= pollMaxAttempts
   193	  ```
   194	  If no non-self-loop matches after exhaustion, the task remains in its current state and `rhei run` aborts the task with a clear error (same behavior as "no matching transition found").
   195	
   196	### Variables for transition conditions
   197	
   198	Polling states expose two additional names alongside the existing `visitCount`
   199	and `visits`:
   200	
   201	- `pollAttempts` — alias for `visitCount` in a poll state (the current attempt index, `1`-based).
   202	- `pollMaxAttempts` — alias for `poll.max_attempts`.
   203	
   204	Both names are available only on transitions whose `from` state declares
   205	`poll:`. Outside a poll state they are undefined.
   206	
   207	### Interaction with other state features
   208	
   209	- **`agent` / `program`.** `poll` works for both. The attempt is one subprocess invocation whose exit code / outputs drive transition matching as usual.
   210	- **`all_targets` / `all_models`.** Fanout composes: each per-target or per-model execution tracks its own `stateVisits.<state-name>` entry (same scoping as `visits`). Slot release applies per fanout invocation.
   211	- **`concurrent`.** Independent: a `concurrent: true` poll state may have multiple tasks in flight simultaneously, each with its own `pollNextAttemptAt`.
   212	- **`agent_timeout` / `program_timeout`.** Bound one attempt's duration; they do not bound the total polling wall-clock time. Combine with `max_attempts` to bound the total.
   213	
   214	## Artifact Contracts
   215	
   216	States may declare required file artifacts as explicit contracts. This lets a
   217	workflow say "review must produce findings" or "fix cannot begin until findings
   218	exist" in machine-readable form rather than relying on prose instructions.
   219	
   220	Each artifact definition has this shape:
   221	
   222	| Field | Type | Required | Description |
   223	|-------|------|----------|-------------|
   224	| `name` | string | Yes | Stable identifier for the artifact within that state |
   225	| `path` | string | Yes | Workspace-relative file path template |
   226	| `description` | string | No | Human-readable explanation of what the artifact contains |
   227	| `optional` | boolean | No | When `true`, a missing file does not block state entry. Only valid on `inputs` entries. Default: `false`. |
   228	
   229	Supported path template variables:
   230	
   231	- `{task_id}` - the current task id as rendered in the plan
   232	- `{state}` - the canonical unsuffixed state name
   233	- `{visit_count}` - the current visit number for counted-loop states (only available when the state declares `visits`)
   234	- `{target}` - the current execution target selector (only available when the state declares `target` or `all_targets`)
   235	- `{target.slug}` - a filesystem-safe slug derived from `{target}` (only available when the state declares `target` or `all_targets`)
   236	- `{agent}` - the current agent id (available when resolved from `target`, `agent`, or settings)
   237	- `{agent.mode}` - the current agent mode (only available when resolved from `target` or `agent_mode`)
   238	- `{model}` - the current model identifier (available when resolved from `target`, `all_targets`, `model`, or `all_models`)
   239	- `{model.provider}` - the resolved provider id for the current model profile
   240	- `{model.name}` - the resolved provider model name for the current model profile
   241	
   242	Runtime semantics:
   243	
   244	- `inputs` are checked before entering the state and before work begins in that
   245	  state. If any required (`optional: false`, the default) input file is missing,
   246	  the transition is rejected. Optional inputs (`optional: true`) are not checked;
   247	  entry proceeds regardless of whether the file exists.
   248	- `outputs` are checked after callbacks complete and before the transition out
   249	  of the state is committed. If any required output file is missing, the
   250	  transition is rejected.
   251	- For every declared input — required or optional — the engine resolves the path
   252	  and checks whether the file exists. The result is exposed as:
   253	  - `{input.<name>.exists}` template variable: `true` or `false`.
   254	  - `RHEI_INPUT_<NAME>_EXISTS` environment variable for programs: `true` or `false`
   255	    (name uppercased, hyphens and spaces replaced with underscores).
   256	- Artifact contracts are file-existence contracts in v1. They do not yet define
   257	  JSON schemas, required headings, or content-level validation.
   258	- Under `orchestrator` [Completion Authority](rhei-agents.spec.md#completion-authority),
   259	  the `outputs:` existence check doubles as the state's deterministic completion
   260	  signal: the subprocess exit alone is not sufficient, and a zero-exit with any
   261	  missing required output leaves the task in its current state. See
   262	  [Completion Condition](rhei-agents.spec.md#completion-condition).
   263	
