    84	### State fields
    85	
    86	Common:
    87	
    88	- `description`
    89	- `instructions` — strongly recommended for every non-terminal state
    90	- `final: true` on terminal states
    91	
    92	> `initial: true` is **not** a state-level field. Initial states are declared on each profile under the top-level `profiles` block; `node_policy` routes each node to a profile.
    93	
    94	Optional workflow controls:
    95	
    96	- `gating: true` for states that require explicit human action to exit
    97	- `personality` for state-specific role framing (overrides the machine-level default)
    98	- `visits: <integer>` for counted loop re-entry limits (minimum `1`)
    99	- `all_models: [<model>, ...]` to run the state once per listed declared model
   100	- `model: <model>` to bind the state to one declared model
   101	- `inputs:` / `outputs:` — artifact contracts (see *Artifact Contracts*)
   102	- `agent:` — overrides the agent id assigned by `rhei next` in this state
   103	
   104	### Transition fields
   105	
   106	Required:
   107	
   108	- `from` — a source state name, or `"*"` for a wildcard (typically used for a global cancellation edge)
   109	- `to`
   110	- `description`
   111	
   112	Optional:
   113	
   114	- `on_leave` — callback invoked on the source state before state change
   115	- `on_enter` — callback invoked on the target state after state change
   116	- `condition` — expression used by `rhei run` to select among multiple outgoing edges
   117	- `exit_code` — routes by subprocess exit code under `rhei run` orchestrator authority
   118	- `timeout`
   119	
   120	Example callback style:
   121	
   122	```yaml
   123	on_leave: "cli:bash ./workflow.sh handoff-review"
   124	```
   125	
   126	### Profiles
   127	
   128	Every machine declares at least one profile. A profile defines the *policy* applied to a node: where it starts and which states it may ever hold.
   129	
   130	```yaml
   131	profiles:
   132	  default:
   133	    initial: <state-name>
   134	    allowed:
   135	      - <state-name>
   136	      - <state-name>
   137	      - ...
   138	```
   139	
   140	Rules:
   141	
   142	- Every profile must declare `initial` and a non-empty `allowed` list.
   143	- The `initial` state must be a member of `allowed`.
   144	- `allowed` must include at least one state with `final: true`.
   145	- For every non-final state in `allowed`, a path to a final state in `allowed` must exist using only transitions whose `to` is also in `allowed`.
   146	
   147	### Node policy
   148	
   149	```yaml
   150	node_policy:
   151	  root: <profile-name>       # required — the plan root (always kind `rhei`) uses this profile
   152	  default: <profile-name>    # required — fallback for non-root kinds not in `by_type` or `overrides`
   153	  by_type:                   # optional — per-kind overrides
   154	    <kind>: <profile-name>
   155	  overrides:                 # optional — ordered, first-match-wins
   156	    - match: { type: <kind>, level: <n> }
   157	      profile: <profile-name>
   158	```
   159	
   160	Rules:
   161	
   162	- `root` and `default` are required and must name defined profiles.
   163	- Every `by_type` key must be a declared non-root node kind. `rhei` is reserved and must never appear as a `by_type` key.
   164	- `overrides` is evaluated in order; the first match wins. Resolution order for a non-root node is `overrides` → `by_type` → `default`.
